snippet.textDisplay:
This should have been an origins movie about the old lady. I have a short idea.

The story takes place in Northern Maine during September, 2019. A former news anchor, now isolated and turned widow, has slowly descended into madness after her son and daughter go away to college earlier that same year. She wants to replace her kids, so she begins stalking some neighborhood childreen, a boy and a girl. They remind her of her own. 

The month is October, and she advertises a Halloween party with candy prizes. The children show up as Hansel and Gretel. It is unclear as to why, out of all the costumes, they would go as that. The old lady, ironically enough, goes as the crazy woman from the same fictional story. The children insist that they can only stay a short while, as their parents will be worried. The young girl suggests that they didn't see their parents on the way out to tell them of their leaving.

Later that same day, while the children are eating their candy and waiting for the rest of the party to arrive, the old woman turns on the news. Police are surrounding the children's home. The mother is seen in the frame, appearing to have been in a serious altercation which left bodily injuries allover. The father is dead.

The police warn the public to be on the lookout for the two children, suggesting their lives are in grave danger. They also remind the public of a recent insane asylum patient that escaped from a New England psychiatric facility toward the end of the summer. They hold up a photo of the old woman.

The TV is subsequently turned off. The young girl, already in total disbelief in light of the news, turns to her left and right, noticing her brother is missing. She turns around, and witnesses the older woman turning up the temperature of a very large oven. The end.

Follow me on my Instagram: poemsandsongsbychris

Thanks for reading 😂
